hopobject.body: Whereabouts are you from? valtrex customer reviews This sleep saves them desperately needed energy, for smaller hummingbirds may sip 1,500 flowers a day, and beating your wings 80 times a second burns a lot of calories. Those wings, connected to their body only at the shoulder joint, rotate 180Â° so the birds can not only hover vertically to feed but also fly backwards and upside down. Thirty per cent of their weight is flight muscles; four per cent is brain, the largest proportion for all birds, so they are the world’s most intelligent bird – well, for their size.
